---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Interactive Model Laboratory"
  description="Interactive mathematical-modeling examples for exploring growth, epidemic dynamics, intervention timing, and stopping distance."
  type="Teaching"
>
  <header class="page-head model-lab-head">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Interactive teaching examples</p>
      <h1>Change an assumption. Watch the model answer differently.</h1>
      <p class="lead">Nine interactive experiments connect equations to behaviour, from foundation models to active research questions. Choose by purpose, then change one assumption and inspect what survives.</p>
      <nav class="model-jump-nav" aria-label="Model laboratory examples">
        <a href="#model-index">Browse all nine</a>
        <a href="#logistic-growth">Foundation experiments</a>
        <a href="/teaching/frontier-model-studio/">Frontier model studio</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="section model-directory-section" id="model-index">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div><p class="eyebrow">Model finder</p><h2>Find the experiment that matches your question.</h2></div>
        <p>Use the two filters or scan the research questions. Every result links directly to the corresponding interactive workbench.</p>
      </div>
      <form class="model-directory-controls" aria-label="Filter interactive models">
        <label for="model-purpose">Question type
          <select id="model-purpose" data-model-filter="purpose">
            <option value="all">All questions</option>
            <option value="systems">Change over time</option>
            <option value="data">Learn from data</option>
            <option value="emergence">Networks and emergence</option>
            <option value="structure">Geometry and structure</option>
            <option value="decision">Scaling and decisions</option>
          </select>
        </label>
        <label for="model-stage">Learning stage
          <select id="model-stage" data-model-filter="stage">
            <option value="all">All stages</option>
            <option value="foundation">Foundation</option>
            <option value="frontier">Research-facing</option>
          </select>
        </label>
      </form>
      <div class="model-library" data-model-library>
        <article data-purpose="systems" data-stage="foundation"><div class="meta-line"><span>Foundation</span><span>Discrete dynamics</span></div><h3><a href="#logistic-growth">Logistic growth</a></h3><p>How does density dependence change exponential growth?</p><a href="#logistic-growth">Start experiment ↓</a></article>
        <article data-purpose="systems" data-stage="foundation"><div class="meta-line"><span>Foundation</span><span>Coupled ODEs</span></div><h3><a href="#sir-intervention">SIR intervention</a></h3><p>How do intervention timing and strength reshape an epidemic curve?</p><a href="#sir-intervention">Start experiment ↓</a></article>
        <article data-purpose="decision" data-stage="foundation"><div class="meta-line"><span>Foundation</span><span>Scaling</span></div><h3><a href="#stopping-distance">Stopping distance</a></h3><p>Why does risk grow faster than speed?</p><a href="#stopping-distance">Start experiment ↓</a></article>
        <article data-purpose="systems" data-stage="frontier"><div class="meta-line"><span>Research-facing</span><span>Bifurcation theory</span></div><h3><a href="/teaching/frontier-model-studio/#critical-transitions">Critical transitions</a></h3><p>When does gradual pressure trigger an abrupt and path-dependent change?</p><a href="/teaching/frontier-model-studio/#critical-transitions">Start experiment →</a></article>
        <article data-purpose="data" data-stage="frontier"><div class="meta-line"><span>Research-facing</span><span>Sparse regression</span></div><h3><a href="/teaching/frontier-model-studio/#equation-discovery">Equation discovery</a></h3><p>Can a governing equation be recovered from noisy observations?</p><a href="/teaching/frontier-model-studio/#equation-discovery">Start experiment →</a></article>
        <article data-purpose="emergence" data-stage="frontier"><div class="meta-line"><span>Research-facing</span><span>Active matter</span></div><h3><a href="/teaching/frontier-model-studio/#collective-motion">Collective motion</a></h3><p>How can local alignment create global order without a leader?</p><a href="/teaching/frontier-model-studio/#collective-motion">Start experiment →</a></article>
        <article data-purpose="emergence" data-stage="frontier"><div class="meta-line"><span>Research-facing</span><span>Higher-order networks</span></div><h3><a href="/teaching/frontier-model-studio/#higher-order-contagion">Higher-order contagion</a></h3><p>What changes when groups, rather than only pairs, transmit influence?</p><a href="/teaching/frontier-model-studio/#higher-order-contagion">Start experiment →</a></article>
        <article data-purpose="data" data-stage="frontier"><div class="meta-line"><span>Research-facing</span><span>Scientific ML</span></div><h3><a href="/teaching/frontier-model-studio/#operator-learning">Operator learning</a></h3><p>What must a reusable model learn to map one function into another?</p><a href="/teaching/frontier-model-studio/#operator-learning">Start experiment →</a></article>
        <article data-purpose="structure" data-stage="frontier"><div class="meta-line"><span>Research-facing</span><span>Topology</span></div><h3><a href="/teaching/frontier-model-studio/#persistent-homology">Persistent homology</a></h3><p>Which shapes survive a change of observational scale?</p><a href="/teaching/frontier-model-studio/#persistent-homology">Start experiment →</a></article>
      </div>
      <p class="small" data-model-count aria-live="polite">Showing all 9 experiments.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script is:inline>
    (() => {
      const purpose = document.querySelector('[data-model-filter="purpose"]');
      const stage = document.querySelector('[data-model-filter="stage"]');
      const cards = [...document.querySelectorAll('[data-model-library] article')];
      const count = document.querySelector('[data-model-count]');
      const filter = () => {
        let visible = 0;
        cards.forEach((card) => {
          const show = (purpose.value === "all" || card.dataset.purpose === purpose.value) && (stage.value === "all" || card.dataset.stage === stage.value);
          card.hidden = !show;
          if (show) visible += 1;
        });
        count.textContent = `Showing ${visible} of ${cards.length} experiments.`;
      };
      purpose.addEventListener("input", filter);
      stage.addEventListener("input", filter);
    })();
  </script>

  <section class="section model-lab-section" id="logistic-growth" data-model="logistic">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="model-intro">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">01 · Discrete dynamics</p>
          <h2>Logistic growth and carrying capacity</h2>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="model-equation" aria-label="P sub n plus one equals P sub n plus r P sub n times one minus P sub n divided by K">P<sub>n+1</sub> = P<sub>n</sub> + rP<sub>n</sub>(1 − P<sub>n</sub>/K)</p>
          <p>The growth term is large when the population is small, then weakens as the state approaches the carrying capacity <em>K</em>. A larger growth rate can create overshoot and alternating corrections.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="model-workbench">
        <form class="model-controls" aria-label="Logistic growth parameters">
          <label for="logistic-initial">Initial population <output for="logistic-initial" data-output="initial">30</output></label>
          <input id="logistic-initial" data-input="initial" type="range" min="10" max="200" step="5" value="30" />

          <label for="logistic-capacity">Carrying capacity <output for="logistic-capacity" data-output="capacity">500</output></label>
          <input id="logistic-capacity" data-input="capacity" type="range" min="200" max="1000" step="50" value="500" />

          <label for="logistic-rate">Growth rate <em>r</em> <output for="logistic-rate" data-output="rate">0.35</output></label>
          <input id="logistic-rate" data-input="rate" type="range" min="0.05" max="1.80" step="0.05" value="0.35" />

          <label for="logistic-steps">Generations <output for="logistic-steps" data-output="steps">50</output></label>
          <input id="logistic-steps" data-input="steps" type="range" min="20" max="80" step="5" value="50" />
        </form>
        <div class="model-visual">
          <svg class="model-chart" data-chart="logistic" viewBox="0 0 720 360" role="img" aria-labelledby="logistic-chart-title logistic-chart-desc"></svg>
          <dl class="model-metrics">
            <div><dt>Final population</dt><dd data-metric="final">—</dd></div>
            <div><dt>Peak population</dt><dd data-metric="peak">—</dd></div>
            <div><dt>First reaches 90% of K</dt><dd data-metric="threshold">—</dd></div>
          </dl>
          <p class="model-reading" data-reading aria-live="polite"></p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="model-prompts">
        <strong>Questions to test</strong>
        <span>Does doubling the initial population halve the time to 90% of <em>K</em>?</span>
        <span>At what value of <em>r</em> does smooth convergence become alternating convergence?</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section model-lab-section" id="sir-intervention" data-model="sir">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="model-intro">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">02 · Coupled differential equations</p>
          <h2>SIR dynamics with a timed intervention</h2>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="model-equation" aria-label="S prime equals negative beta S I divided by N; I prime equals beta S I divided by N minus gamma I; R prime equals gamma I">S′ = −βSI/N &nbsp; · &nbsp; I′ = βSI/N − γI &nbsp; · &nbsp; R′ = γI</p>
          <p>The model divides a fixed population of 1,000 into susceptible, infectious, and removed groups. On the selected intervention day, transmission <em>β</em> is reduced by the chosen percentage.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="model-workbench">
        <form class="model-controls" aria-label="SIR model parameters">
          <label for="sir-initial">Initial infectious people <output for="sir-initial" data-output="initial">10</output></label>
          <input id="sir-initial" data-input="initial" type="range" min="1" max="50" step="1" value="10" />

          <label for="sir-beta">Transmission rate β <output for="sir-beta" data-output="beta">0.32</output> per day</label>
          <input id="sir-beta" data-input="beta" type="range" min="0.10" max="0.80" step="0.01" value="0.32" />

          <label for="sir-duration">Mean infectious period <output for="sir-duration" data-output="duration">7</output> days</label>
          <input id="sir-duration" data-input="duration" type="range" min="3" max="14" step="1" value="7" />

          <label for="sir-day">Intervention day <output for="sir-day" data-output="day">28</output></label>
          <input id="sir-day" data-input="day" type="range" min="5" max="100" step="1" value="28" />

          <label for="sir-reduction">Transmission reduction <output for="sir-reduction" data-output="reduction">45</output>%</label>
          <input id="sir-reduction" data-input="reduction" type="range" min="0" max="80" step="5" value="45" />
        </form>
        <div class="model-visual">
          <div class="model-legend" aria-hidden="true"><span class="legend-s">Susceptible</span><span class="legend-i">Infectious</span><span class="legend-r">Removed</span><span class="legend-intervention">Intervention</span></div>
          <svg class="model-chart" data-chart="sir" viewBox="0 0 720 360" role="img" aria-labelledby="sir-chart-title sir-chart-desc"></svg>
          <dl class="model-metrics">
            <div><dt>Initial R₀</dt><dd data-metric="r0">—</dd></div>
            <div><dt>Peak infectious</dt><dd data-metric="peak">—</dd></div>
            <div><dt>Peak day</dt><dd data-metric="peak-day">—</dd></div>
          </dl>
          <p class="model-reading" data-reading aria-live="polite"></p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="model-prompts">
        <strong>Questions to test</strong>
        <span>Can a late, strong intervention produce a higher peak than an early, moderate one?</span>
        <span>Which conclusion changes when the infectious period is uncertain?</span>
      </div>
      <p class="small">This is a deliberately simplified teaching model, not an epidemiological forecast or medical recommendation.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section model-lab-section" id="stopping-distance" data-model="stopping">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="model-intro">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">03 · Scaling and decomposition</p>
          <h2>Why stopping distance grows faster than speed</h2>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="model-equation" aria-label="d equals v t sub r plus v squared divided by two mu g">d(v) = vt<sub>r</sub> + v²/(2μg)</p>
          <p>Reaction distance grows linearly with speed; braking distance grows quadratically. The decomposition shows why a modest increase in speed can create a much larger increase in total distance.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="model-workbench">
        <form class="model-controls" aria-label="Stopping-distance parameters">
          <label for="stop-speed">Speed <output for="stop-speed" data-output="speed">60</output> km/h</label>
          <input id="stop-speed" data-input="speed" type="range" min="20" max="120" step="5" value="60" />

          <label for="stop-reaction">Reaction time <output for="stop-reaction" data-output="reaction">1.2</output> s</label>
          <input id="stop-reaction" data-input="reaction" type="range" min="0.5" max="2.5" step="0.1" value="1.2" />

          <label for="stop-friction">Tyre–road friction μ <output for="stop-friction" data-output="friction">0.70</output></label>
          <input id="stop-friction" data-input="friction" type="range" min="0.30" max="0.90" step="0.05" value="0.70" />
        </form>
        <div class="model-visual">
          <div class="model-legend" aria-hidden="true"><span class="legend-total">Total</span><span class="legend-reaction">Reaction</span><span class="legend-braking">Braking</span></div>
          <svg class="model-chart" data-chart="stopping" viewBox="0 0 720 360" role="img" aria-labelledby="stopping-chart-title stopping-chart-desc"></svg>
          <dl class="model-metrics">
            <div><dt>Reaction distance</dt><dd data-metric="reaction">—</dd></div>
            <div><dt>Braking distance</dt><dd data-metric="braking">—</dd></div>
            <div><dt>Total distance</dt><dd data-metric="total">—</dd></div>
          </dl>
          <p class="model-reading" data-reading aria-live="polite"></p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="model-prompts">
        <strong>Questions to test</strong>
        <span>Does doubling speed double total stopping distance?</span>
        <span>When does reaction time matter more than road friction?</span>
      </div>
      <p class="small">The formula is a classroom baseline on a level road with constant friction. Real stopping distance also depends on gradient, tyres, brakes, weather, perception, and driver behaviour.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container teaching-contact">
      <div><p class="eyebrow">From interaction to evidence</p><h2>A slider movement is a hypothesis, not a conclusion.</h2></div>
      <div><p>Use each example to record one prediction, one parameter change, one observed response, and one limitation. That four-line record turns exploration into a small modeling experiment.</p><a class="button secondary" href="/teaching/mathematical-modeling-lecture-programme/">Return to the lecture programme</a></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script is:inline>
    (() => {
      const margin = { left: 62, right: 24, top: 24, bottom: 48 };
      const width = 720;
      const height = 360;
      const plotWidth = width - margin.left - margin.right;
      const plotHeight = height - margin.top - margin.bottom;

      const number = (value, digits = 0) => Number(value).toFixed(digits);
      const read = (root, name) => Number(root.querySelector(`[data-input="${name}"]`).value);
      const write = (root, selector, value) => { root.querySelector(selector).textContent = value; };
      const pointsPath = (points, xMax, yMax) => points.map((point, index) => {
        const x = margin.left + (point.x / xMax) * plotWidth;
        const y = margin.top + plotHeight - (point.y / yMax) * plotHeight;
        return `${index ? "L" : "M"}${x.toFixed(2)},${y.toFixed(2)}`;
      }).join(" ");
      const areaPath = (points, xMax, yMax) => {
        const firstX = margin.left + (points[0].x / xMax) * plotWidth;
        const lastX = margin.left + (points.at(-1).x / xMax) * plotWidth;
        const baseline = margin.top + plotHeight;
        return `${pointsPath(points, xMax, yMax)} L${lastX.toFixed(2)},${baseline} L${firstX.toFixed(2)},${baseline} Z`;
      };

      const chartFrame = (xMax, yMax, xLabel, yLabel) => {
        const xTicks = 4;
        const yTicks = 4;
        let markup = `<rect class="chart-field" x="${margin.left}" y="${margin.top}" width="${plotWidth}" height="${plotHeight}" rx="12"></rect>`;
        for (let index = 0; index <= xTicks; index += 1) {
          const value = (xMax * index) / xTicks;
          const x = margin.left + (plotWidth * index) / xTicks;
          markup += `<line class="chart-grid chart-grid-x" x1="${x}" y1="${margin.top}" x2="${x}" y2="${margin.top + plotHeight}"></line>`;
          markup += `<text class="chart-tick" x="${x}" y="${height - 22}" text-anchor="middle">${Math.round(value)}</text>`;
        }
        for (let index = 0; index <= yTicks; index += 1) {
          const value = (yMax * index) / yTicks;
          const y = margin.top + plotHeight - (plotHeight * index) / yTicks;
          markup += `<line class="chart-grid chart-grid-y" x1="${margin.left}" y1="${y}" x2="${margin.left + plotWidth}" y2="${y}"></line>`;
          markup += `<text class="chart-tick" x="${margin.left - 10}" y="${y + 4}" text-anchor="end">${Math.round(value)}</text>`;
        }
        markup += `<line class="chart-axis" x1="${margin.left}" y1="${margin.top + plotHeight}" x2="${margin.left + plotWidth}" y2="${margin.top + plotHeight}"></line>`;
        markup += `<line class="chart-axis" x1="${margin.left}" y1="${margin.top}" x2="${margin.left}" y2="${margin.top + plotHeight}"></line>`;
        markup += `<text class="chart-label" x="${margin.left + plotWidth / 2}" y="${height - 4}" text-anchor="middle">${xLabel}</text>`;
        markup += `<text class="chart-label" transform="translate(16 ${margin.top + plotHeight / 2}) rotate(-90)" text-anchor="middle">${yLabel}</text>`;
        return markup;
      };

      const bindControls = (root, render) => {
        root.querySelectorAll('input[type="range"]').forEach((input) => input.addEventListener("input", render));
        render();
      };

      const logisticRoot = document.querySelector('[data-model="logistic"]');
      const renderLogistic = () => {
        const initial = read(logisticRoot, "initial");
        const capacity = read(logisticRoot, "capacity");
        const rate = read(logisticRoot, "rate");
        const steps = read(logisticRoot, "steps");
        write(logisticRoot, '[data-output="initial"]', number(initial));
        write(logisticRoot, '[data-output="capacity"]', number(capacity));
        write(logisticRoot, '[data-output="rate"]', number(rate, 2));
        write(logisticRoot, '[data-output="steps"]', number(steps));

        const values = [{ x: 0, y: initial }];
        for (let step = 1; step <= steps; step += 1) {
          const current = values[step - 1].y;
          const next = Math.max(0, current + rate * current * (1 - current / capacity));
          values.push({ x: step, y: next });
        }
        const peak = Math.max(...values.map((point) => point.y));
        const threshold = values.find((point) => point.y >= 0.9 * capacity);
        const yMax = Math.max(capacity * 1.12, peak * 1.08);
        const svg = logisticRoot.querySelector('[data-chart="logistic"]');
        const finalX = margin.left + plotWidth;
        const finalY = margin.top + plotHeight - (values.at(-1).y / yMax) * plotHeight;
        svg.innerHTML = `<title id="logistic-chart-title">Logistic population over discrete generations</title><desc id="logistic-chart-desc">The line updates when initial population, carrying capacity, growth rate, or number of generations changes.</desc>${chartFrame(steps, yMax, "Generation n", "Population P")}<path class="series-area logistic-area" d="${areaPath(values, steps, yMax)}"></path><line class="capacity-line" x1="${margin.left}" y1="${margin.top + plotHeight - (capacity / yMax) * plotHeight}" x2="${margin.left + plotWidth}" y2="${margin.top + plotHeight - (capacity / yMax) * plotHeight}"></line><text class="capacity-label" x="${margin.left + plotWidth - 4}" y="${margin.top + plotHeight - (capacity / yMax) * plotHeight - 8}" text-anchor="end">carrying capacity K = ${capacity}</text><path class="series-logistic" d="${pointsPath(values, steps, yMax)}"></path><circle class="series-end logistic-end" cx="${finalX}" cy="${finalY}" r="5"></circle>`;
        write(logisticRoot, '[data-metric="final"]', number(values.at(-1).y, 1));
        write(logisticRoot, '[data-metric="peak"]', number(peak, 1));
        write(logisticRoot, '[data-metric="threshold"]', threshold ? `generation ${threshold.x}` : "not reached");
        const overshoot = peak > capacity * 1.01;
        const reading = overshoot
          ? `With r = ${number(rate, 2)}, the population overshoots K and corrects in later generations. The carrying capacity is an equilibrium, not a hard ceiling.`
          : threshold
            ? `The trajectory first reaches 90% of K at generation ${threshold.x}. Growth slows because the remaining capacity term becomes small.`
            : `The trajectory remains below 90% of K within ${steps} generations. A longer horizon is needed before claiming convergence.`;
        write(logisticRoot, "[data-reading]", reading);
      };
      bindControls(logisticRoot, renderLogistic);

      const sirRoot = document.querySelector('[data-model="sir"]');
      const renderSir = () => {
        const population = 1000;
        const initial = read(sirRoot, "initial");
        const beta = read(sirRoot, "beta");
        const duration = read(sirRoot, "duration");
        const gamma = 1 / duration;
        const interventionDay = read(sirRoot, "day");
        const reduction = read(sirRoot, "reduction") / 100;
        write(sirRoot, '[data-output="initial"]', number(initial));
        write(sirRoot, '[data-output="beta"]', number(beta, 2));
        write(sirRoot, '[data-output="duration"]', number(duration));
        write(sirRoot, '[data-output="day"]', number(interventionDay));
        write(sirRoot, '[data-output="reduction"]', number(reduction * 100));

        const dt = 0.2;
        const days = 160;
        let susceptible = population - initial;
        let infectious = initial;
        let removed = 0;
        const values = [{ x: 0, susceptible, infectious, removed }];
        for (let time = dt; time <= days + 0.0001; time += dt) {
          const betaNow = time >= interventionDay ? beta * (1 - reduction) : beta;
          const newInfections = Math.min(susceptible, betaNow * susceptible * infectious / population * dt);
          const newRemoved = Math.min(infectious + newInfections, gamma * infectious * dt);
          susceptible -= newInfections;
          infectious += newInfections - newRemoved;
          removed += newRemoved;
          values.push({ x: time, susceptible, infectious, removed });
        }
        const sampled = values.filter((_, index) => index % 5 === 0);
        const sPoints = sampled.map((point) => ({ x: point.x, y: point.susceptible }));
        const iPoints = sampled.map((point) => ({ x: point.x, y: point.infectious }));
        const rPoints = sampled.map((point) => ({ x: point.x, y: point.removed }));
        const peak = values.reduce((best, point) => point.infectious > best.infectious ? point : best, values[0]);
        const interventionX = margin.left + (interventionDay / days) * plotWidth;
        const svg = sirRoot.querySelector('[data-chart="sir"]');
        const peakX = margin.left + (peak.x / days) * plotWidth;
        const peakY = margin.top + plotHeight - (peak.infectious / population) * plotHeight;
        svg.innerHTML = `<title id="sir-chart-title">SIR epidemic trajectories with a timed intervention</title><desc id="sir-chart-desc">Susceptible, infectious, and removed populations over 160 days. A vertical line marks the selected intervention day.</desc>${chartFrame(days, population, "Day", "People")}<path class="series-area sir-area" d="${areaPath(iPoints, days, population)}"></path><path class="series-s" d="${pointsPath(sPoints, days, population)}"></path><path class="series-i" d="${pointsPath(iPoints, days, population)}"></path><path class="series-r" d="${pointsPath(rPoints, days, population)}"></path><line class="intervention-line" x1="${interventionX}" y1="${margin.top}" x2="${interventionX}" y2="${margin.top + plotHeight}"></line><text class="intervention-label" x="${interventionX + 6}" y="${margin.top + 17}">intervention · day ${interventionDay}</text><circle class="series-end sir-end" cx="${peakX}" cy="${peakY}" r="5"></circle>`;
        const r0 = beta / gamma;
        const after = beta * (1 - reduction) / gamma;
        write(sirRoot, '[data-metric="r0"]', number(r0, 2));
        write(sirRoot, '[data-metric="peak"]', `${number(peak.infectious)} people`);
        write(sirRoot, '[data-metric="peak-day"]', number(peak.x, 1));
        const reading = after < 1
          ? `The intervention changes β/γ from ${number(r0, 2)} to ${number(after, 2)}, below 1 in the fully susceptible approximation. Timing still matters because infections accumulated before day ${interventionDay} cannot be undone.`
          : `After intervention, β/γ is ${number(after, 2)}. In the fully susceptible approximation it remains above 1, so the intervention slows transmission without immediately reversing growth.`;
        write(sirRoot, "[data-reading]", reading);
      };
      bindControls(sirRoot, renderSir);

      const stoppingRoot = document.querySelector('[data-model="stopping"]');
      const distances = (speedKmh, reactionTime, friction) => {
        const speed = speedKmh / 3.6;
        const reaction = speed * reactionTime;
        const braking = speed * speed / (2 * friction * 9.81);
        return { reaction, braking, total: reaction + braking };
      };
      const renderStopping = () => {
        const speed = read(stoppingRoot, "speed");
        const reactionTime = read(stoppingRoot, "reaction");
        const friction = read(stoppingRoot, "friction");
        write(stoppingRoot, '[data-output="speed"]', number(speed));
        write(stoppingRoot, '[data-output="reaction"]', number(reactionTime, 1));
        write(stoppingRoot, '[data-output="friction"]', number(friction, 2));

        const speeds = Array.from({ length: 61 }, (_, index) => index * 2);
        const totalPoints = speeds.map((value) => ({ x: value, y: distances(value, reactionTime, friction).total }));
        const reactionPoints = speeds.map((value) => ({ x: value, y: distances(value, reactionTime, friction).reaction }));
        const brakingPoints = speeds.map((value) => ({ x: value, y: distances(value, reactionTime, friction).braking }));
        const selected = distances(speed, reactionTime, friction);
        const yMax = Math.ceil(totalPoints.at(-1).y / 20) * 20;
        const selectedX = margin.left + (speed / 120) * plotWidth;
        const selectedY = margin.top + plotHeight - (selected.total / yMax) * plotHeight;
        const svg = stoppingRoot.querySelector('[data-chart="stopping"]');
        svg.innerHTML = `<title id="stopping-chart-title">Stopping distance by speed</title><desc id="stopping-chart-desc">Total, reaction, and braking distance curves from zero to 120 kilometres per hour. A point marks the selected speed.</desc>${chartFrame(120, yMax, "Speed (km/h)", "Distance (m)")}<path class="series-area stopping-area" d="${areaPath(totalPoints, 120, yMax)}"></path><path class="series-total" d="${pointsPath(totalPoints, 120, yMax)}"></path><path class="series-reaction" d="${pointsPath(reactionPoints, 120, yMax)}"></path><path class="series-braking" d="${pointsPath(brakingPoints, 120, yMax)}"></path><circle class="selected-point" cx="${selectedX}" cy="${selectedY}" r="6"></circle><text class="selected-label" x="${Math.min(selectedX + 12, margin.left + plotWidth - 92)}" y="${Math.max(selectedY - 12, margin.top + 17)}">${speed} km/h · ${number(selected.total, 1)} m</text>`;
        write(stoppingRoot, '[data-metric="reaction"]', `${number(selected.reaction, 1)} m`);
        write(stoppingRoot, '[data-metric="braking"]', `${number(selected.braking, 1)} m`);
        write(stoppingRoot, '[data-metric="total"]', `${number(selected.total, 1)} m`);
        const doubled = distances(Math.min(speed * 2, 120), reactionTime, friction).total;
        const comparison = speed <= 60 ? ` At ${Math.min(speed * 2, 120)} km/h the same baseline gives ${number(doubled, 1)} m, not merely twice the distance.` : " The upward curvature is the visible signature of the v² braking term.";
        write(stoppingRoot, "[data-reading]", `At ${speed} km/h, braking contributes ${number(100 * selected.braking / selected.total)}% of the modeled total.${comparison}`);
      };
      bindControls(stoppingRoot, renderStopping);
    })();
  </script>
</BaseLayout>
